### Project 3: 📊 "SynthReason" — Synthetic Reasoning Dataset Generator with Quality Filtering

**Why this wins the job:** Shows you can generate AND curate high-quality reasoning data at scale — the end-to-end pipeline Alignerr operates.

#### What You Build
A pipeline that uses frontier models to generate thousands of reasoning traces for complex tasks (math, coding, logic puzzles), then automatically filters out low-quality traces using verification, producing a clean, fine-tuning-ready dataset.

#### Architecture
```
synth_reason/
├── generator/
│   ├── task_sampler.py          # Samples diverse tasks from seed datasets
│   ├── trace_generator.py       # Generates CoT traces via API (GPT-4, Claude, etc.)
│   ├── difficulty_calibrator.py # Ensures task difficulty distribution
│   └── prompt_engineering/
│       ├── math_prompts.py
│       ├── coding_prompts.py
│       └── logic_prompts.py
├── verifier/
│   ├── code_verifier.py         # Executes code solutions to verify correctness
│   ├── math_verifier.py         # Checks mathematical answers against ground truth
│   ├── contradiction_detector.py # Flags internal contradictions in reasoning
│   └── hallucination_checker.py # Cross-references claims against knowledge base
├── filter/
│   ├── quality_filter.py        # Composite filter combining all checks
│   ├── diversity_sampler.py     # Ensures dataset diversity (topics, difficulty, length)
│   └── deduplicator.py          # Removes near-duplicate traces
├── analysis/
│   ├── dataset_statistics.py    # Generates comprehensive dataset report
│   └── quality_dashboard.py     # Streamlit dashboard for dataset exploration
├── output/
│   ├── filtered_dataset.jsonl   # Clean, ready-to-use dataset
│   └── rejection_log.jsonl      # Traces that failed filters with reasons
├── README.md
└── requirements.txt
```

#### The Pipeline
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Seed Tasks<br>Math/Code/Logic] --> B[Trace Generation<br>via Frontier LLMs]
    B --> C[Verification<br>Execute code, check answers]
